'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH KAFSDUMP 8 "2026-03-17" "kafs 0.4.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
kafsdump \- inspect offline KAFS image metadata without mutation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kafsdump
.RB [ --json ]
.I image
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kafsdump
reads an offline KAFS image in read-only mode and prints a compact metadata summary.
The tool never writes image contents.
.SH OUTPUT
The dump contains the following sections:
.TP
.B superblock
Magic/version, block geometry, and free counters.
.TP
.B inode_summary
Inode totals, used/free counts, and number of in-use inodes with link count 0.
.TP
.B hrl_summary
HRL entry totals, live entry count, and refcount sum.
.TP
.B journal_header
In-image journal header fields and header CRC validation result.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Emit machine-readable JSON instead of text output.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Dump completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
I/O or format-boundary error.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kafs (1),
.BR kafsctl (1),
.BR mkfs.kafs (8),
.BR fsck.kafs (8),
.BR kafsimage (8),
.BR kafsresize (8),
.BR kafs-info (8)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
